w hotkey and wanted to share the idea here and see what experiences other clerics have of it....<br>
<br>
/sit off<br>
/cast 3 [Stun (level 4 version)]<br>
/pause 16<br>
/sit on<br>
<br>
This hotkey I press every time the stun spell recycles and keeps the monster stunned for about 1/3rd of the fight.  The reduction in damage <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> seems</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to be more mana efficient than healing the damage.<br>
<br>
The beauty of the basic stun is that it will not interupt mez if you screw up and hit the wrong mob, it doesn't burn much mana for the stun duration and also doesn't generate THAT much agro, although you will be higher up the list than normal.<br>
<br>
I was hoping some other clerics would experiment with this in different situations and perhaps we can compare notes.<br>
<br>
It certainly has not prooved efficient if I get a few resists during the fight but without clarity when I was 53rd in Chardok, it seemed to have an overall mana saving of about 20-30% with a 52 Warrior tank (Warrmouk).<br>
<br>
I suspect with clarity running the lost med time would outweigh the saving in damage.<br>
<br>
Pneumatic, 54th Disciple of Innoruk, Vicar of Hatred, Purple Kitten.<br>
